radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits; no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation with no focal lesions; mild periportal edema present. The pancreas is normal with no focal lesions. The spleen is normal in size and attenuation. The kidneys are of normal size with no focal lesions. There is a dilated fluid-filled 8 mm structure likely representing the appendix. Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis. Diffuse endometrial thickening of indeterminate nature. No lymphadenopathy or vascular abnormalities noted. No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
